  "response": "Let the three angles of the triangle be $2x$, $3x$, and $4x$. The sum of the angles in a triangle is 180 degrees. Therefore, we have:\n$$2x + 3x + 4x = 180$$\n$$9x = 180$$\n$$x = \\frac{180}{9}$$\n$$x = 20$$\nThe angles are:\n$2x = 2(20) = 40$ degrees\n$3x = 3(20) = 60$ degrees\n$4x = 4(20) = 80$ degrees\nThe three angles are 40, 60, and 80 degrees. The smallest angle is $2x = 40$ degrees.\n\nFinal Answer: The final answer is $\\boxed{40}$",
